10/09/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- In several interviews at the weekend, US Ambassador to BiH Douglas McElhaney urged Bosnian politicians to wage constructive campaigns in the run-up to the 1 October elections, and to focus on current issues, instead of referring to the past. He said nationalistic statements are not relevant in a country focused on reforms and Euro-Atlantic integration. In particular, he dismissed the idea of Republika Srpska holding an independence referendum.
In other news, NATO troops assisted by the EU Police Mission in BiH searched houses and business facilities owned by the family of war crimes fugitive Stojan Zupljanin in the Banja Luka area Friday (8 September). His son, Mladen, is believed to be an actively helping Zupljanin avoid arrest and extradition to the UN tribunal in The Hague. (Nezavisne novine, Dnevni avaz, PBS BiH - 09/09/06; PBS BiH - 08/09/06)
